The Swiss National Bank bought dollarsand sold yen in concerted action along with the Bundesbank andthe U.S. Federal Reserve Board, a bank spokesman told Reuters.    "We intervened in dollar-yen with the Bundesbank and theFed," he said. He declined to specify the extent of theintervention, which took place at around 1200 GMT, afterreports by Frankfurt dealers the Bundesbank was in the market.    The intervention failed to prevent the dollar dipping to1.4548 Swiss francs at around 1320 GMT, close to its all-timelow of 1.4510 francs set on September 26, 1978. It thensteadied to 1.4560/75 francs. REUTER&#3;